          {
            "segment": {
              "endIndex": 81,
              "text": "The general rule of thumb is to get a professional facial **every 4 to 6 weeks**."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              0,
              1,
              2,
              3,
              4,
              5
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 83,
              "endIndex": 276,
              "text": "This timeframe isn't arbitrary; it is designed to align with your skin's natural **cell turnover cycle**, which is the process of your skin shedding dead cells and replacing them with new ones."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              6,
              7,
              0,
              8,
              4,
              9
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 341,
              "endIndex": 444,
              "text": "However, the \"perfect\" frequency depends on your specific skin type, your age, and your skincare goals."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              10
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 453,
              "endIndex": 475,
              "text": "Frequency by Skin Type"
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              11,
              12,
              3,
              2,
              5,
              4,
              0,
              1
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 476,
              "endIndex": 666,
              "text": "*   **Oily or Acne-Prone Skin:** **Every 2 to 4 weeks.** During active breakout phases, more frequent sessions (including extractions and light peels) help clear out congestion and bacteria."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              12
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 667,
              "endIndex": 740,
              "text": "Once the skin stabilizes, you can move to a monthly maintenance schedule."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              13
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 741,
              "endIndex": 948,
              "text": "*   **Normal, Dry, or Combination Skin:** **Every 4 to 6 weeks.** A monthly \"reset\" is usually enough to deep-clean pores, remove the month’s buildup of dead skin, and provide professional-grade hydration."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              3
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 949,
              "endIndex": 1090,
              "text": "*   **Sensitive Skin:** **Every 6 to 8 weeks.** Sensitive skin has a more delicate barrier and needs more time to recover between treatments."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              5
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 1091,
              "endIndex": 1178,
              "text": "Over-exfoliating sensitive skin can lead to redness, burning, and increased reactivity."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              5
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 1187,
              "endIndex": 1303,
              "text": "Frequency by Age\nAs you age, your skin cell turnover slows down, which can make your complexion look dull or uneven."
            },
            "groundingChunkIndices": [
              8,
              6,
              14,
              11,
              0
            ]
          },
          {
            "segment": {
              "startIndex": 1304,
              "endIndex": 1396,
